description: Melchizedek and Evangeline confront a muscled man who battles a team of heroes called The Humanitarian Guild.
name: Chapter 1

description: A pleasant writers' retreat becomes a snowbound fear factory as a prominent author is murdered, and it falls to youth sleuth Charlotte Grote to unpick the web of lies, deceit, smoking and ROMANCE.
The Ninja chases a lead to recover the lost weapon but he gets more than he bargained for.

From the dawn of the 20th Century came a new chapter in mankind's history, unleashed during a time of great war and destruction. It was the beginning of the Age of the SUPERPOWERS, yet with the closing of the Second World War, this new spark seemingly flickered and died. Until now... Now the story can be told of the great lost SUPERPOWERS -- men and women with incredible abilities who changed the course of mankind forever...and who had been thought lost ...Until now... DYNAMITE ENTERTAINMENT and Alex Ross unleash the SUPERPOWERS! This explosive series features story crafted by Justice collaborators Alex Ross and Jim Kruger, joined by artists Stephen Sadowksi, Doug Klauba, Carlos Paul, Deborah Carita and additional art by Alex Ross. The story of SUPERPOWERS begins here and as our story unfolds, we journey to the heights and depths of the Second World War and present day and come face-to-face with the great forgotten heroes of the ages, and solve the mystery of where these legends disappeared to after the great war. This special collected edition features PROJECT SUPERPOWERS #0-7, character bios and art by Alex Ross, Ross sketches, designs and unseen artwork.
name: TPB

description: This special story by Alex Ross and Joe Casey invites you to "Meet the Bad Guys!" As the Golden Age heroes return, the villains rise! Illustrated by Jonathan Lau, Mike Lilly, and others, and featuring the Green Lama and the debut of Blood Lust, this collection spinning out of Alex Ross' Project Superpowers includes character sketches and a complete cover gallery.
name: TPB

volume.name: Project Superpowers: Meet the Bad Guys

description:
Who are the Rat Queens?

A pack of booze-guzzling, death-dealing battle maidens-for-hire, and they're in the business of killing all gods' creatures for profit. It's also a darkly comedic fantasy series starring Hannah the Rockabilly Elven Mage, Violet the Hipster Dwarven Fighter, Dee the Atheist Human Cleric and Betty the Hippy Hobbit Thief.

This modern spin on an old school genre is a violent monster-killing epic that is like Buffy meets Tank Girl in a Lord of the Rings world on crack!

A new ongoing series from PETER PANZERFAUST's KURTIS J. WIEBE and artist ROC UPCHURCH and now your chance to get a taste of it for FREE.

This FREE PREVIEW is ONLY available digitally and features exclusive RAT QUEENS tales that won't be in the first issue!

When young Sylvia Sloane is murdered by an evil spirit, she is given a second chance at life by a mysterious force. Reborn as THE SAPPHIRE SPECTRE, a being of pure concentrated ethereal energy, Sylvia can choose to both live her normal life as well as traverse the eerie terrain of the spirit plane to restore balance between the world of the living and the dead. Prepare yourself for 120 pages of action, adventure and horror as you follow THE SAPPHIRE SPECTRE, her best friend Melissa and the mysterious Mr. Black from urban Chicago to hell and back again. Snapshots allowed, but she won't show up on film.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: The Sapphire Spectre: You Only Die Twice

description:
WHY WE LOVE IT: Sons Of Anarchy has captivated the attention of the entire BOOM! team with its smart plotting, compelling characters, and modern vision of the outlaw genre. We love the show so much we couldn’t wait to help expand the world of SAMCRO.

WHY YOU’LL LOVE IT: Gun-smuggling outlaw bikers with complex pasts and gripping personalities. If you love “guys with guns” like we do, this is that genre at its most elevated.

WHAT IT’S ABOUT: With no one else to turn to, the daughter of an old SAMCRO member comes to Charming looking for help. The only people standing between Kendra and certain death are the Sons of Anarchy, and, for better or for worse, Sergeant-at-Arms Tig.

The prestigious High School of Fashion and Design attracts the best and brightest future fashion stars in Los Angeles; to stand even a chance of making it, you can't go it alone. Best friends Claire, Ashley, Sue-Ni, Ruby and Kaya are there for each other and they're ready to take the fashion world by storm. Whether it's fashion design, interiors, or new technologies, these four have the unique skills and the passion they'll need to change the game . . .

. . . and to save the world! As the girls uncover a sinister plot to rob the earth of its most precious resource they'll have to marshall strange abilities they once thought were confined to myths and legends - and more importantly, they'll have to watch each other's backs.

Note: The digital edition (9/11/2013) for this volume was released two weeks before the print edition (9/25/2013).
name: Vol. 1

description: Directly beneath ROLAND GARROS, the French Open stadium, is a top secret underground facility that houses a high-tech training complex. The complex's purpose is to train planet Earth's young tennis prodigies in the game of turbo tennis, an intergalactic form of tennis which is taking the Milky Way by storm. For several generations now, the most talented young players on Earth have competed in TURBOTEN. The greatest Turbo Tennis tournament of all time, it pits pits the greatest champions from all the galaxies against each other.
name: Volume 1

description: Captain Flemm returns to Port Royal to buy a new ship and encounters the local witch doctor and what he thinks is a lucky hat.

Years after the battle of the Alamo, Mickey Mouse has decided to leave Texas for Oregon. At Fort Laramie, he meets the beautiful Clementine, who is also set on leaving those desolate lands and going west! They join a caravan, led by a very shady fellow, Pegwood...
name: Mickey Mouse and the Route to Oregon

volume.name: Once Upon A Time... in America

description: The race West in search of new territory has begun! Not wanting to be left out, Mickey Mouse sets out to cross the big Sierra Nevadas! Upon reaching California, Mickey stays with a peaceful Native American tribe who live in harmony with nature. But their tranquillity is jeopardized by the sudden gold fever sweeping through the settlers coming West!
name: Mickey Mouse and the Gold Rush

volume.name: Once Upon A Time... in America

description: After wandering through the desert, Mickey Mouse finally makes it to one of the many cities founded by the settlers during the gold rush! There, he meets old friends who are victims of injustice at the hands of a group of bandits...
name: Mickey Mouse and the Law of the Wild West

volume.name: Once Upon A Time... in America

description: Mickey Mouse arrives in Texas and finds a job in a ranch, whose owner is...Clementine! Life at the ranch is not easy, however, and Mickey decides to help Clementine get to a more prosperous place...
name: Mickey Mouse and the Long Track

volume.name: Once Upon A Time... in America

description: After moving to a big city in the east with Clementine, Mickey Mouse decides to go back and visit his old friend Goof Carson in Texas! Many things have changed…this is the time of great inventions, which the old cowboys find difficult to accept!
name: Mickey Mouse and the Last Cowboy

volume.name: Once Upon A Time... in America

description: Greetings, potential buyer! Do you like failing, miserably? Well, good news! Because now there's a book that's been made just for you: The Cartoon Guidebook To Absolute Failure. Written by Erik Craddock, and Illustrated by Logan Faerber. In the first issue, learn how to fail at such topics as fending off vampires, stopping grizzly bear attacks, slaying a dragon, mowing your lawn, and so much more!
name: Vampires, Grizzly Bears, and Zombie Uprisings!

volume.name: The Cartoon Guidebook to Absolute Failure

description: Greetings again, potential buyer! It's The Cartoon Guidebook To Absolute Failure. Written by Erik Craddock, and Illustrated by Logan Faerber. In this second action-packed issue, learn how to fail at such topics as being a ninja, thwarting a super villain, performing open heart surgery, directing a summer movie blockbuster, and so much more!
name: Video Games, Greek Mythology, and Alien Armadas!

volume.name: The Cartoon Guidebook to Absolute Failure

description: Olympia's greatest hunter, Orion sits as the centuries turn to millennia. Torn between his resentment of the Pantheon, his crumbling faith and his need to serve them, Orion seeks the ultimate purpose of his immortal life and is thrust in the middle of a conspiracy that can destroy Olympus. Orion delves into the dark underbelly of Greek mythos -- the rumblings of a massive war between the Olympians and the lesser gods sits on the shoulders of a long ignored demi-god whom both sides see as the key.

A cancer is eating away at the Pantheon's influence over the mortal world. Far from

their glory days 3000 years in the past, a new struggle for dominance erupts between the older gods and their offspring ... and Orion is caught in the middle. Orion needs to find the missing Eye of the Oracle before it falls into the wrong hands and he must look into his painful past to find it... a journey that will lead him directly to the mouth of Hades. Second of the four-part series.

To tempt the Fates is one thing. To out and out steal from them is sheer lunacy. Yet

Orion must pit his destiny against some of the fiercest and most dangerous forces Olympus has to offer. As he peels away another veil of the gods' deceit, Orion is forced to walk the precipice between myth and mystery only to find himself at the very mouth of Hades.
The final chapter of Orion the Hunter. Orion delves into the underbelly of Hades to stop the war of the Olympians while also trying to save the earth.

Get caught up with Alex Ross' Project Superpowers: Chapter 2 for just $9.99!!!!!!! There is no excuse to miss out on the Alex Ross project of the year! Tell a friend! Actually, tell a LOT of friends and ask your retailer to stock lots of copies! At $9.99 this is priced to get more readers to this great series! Overseen again by Alex Ross, who plots and art directs the entire PROJECT SUPERPOWERS universe, writer Jim Krueger returns for Chapter Two, as the pair of all-star creators are joined for the series by Edgar (DEATH DEFYING 'DEVIL) Salazar! PROJECT SUPERPOWERS: CHAPTER TWO picks up from the events of CHAPTER ONE as the newly returned heroes have set out on a quest to use their newfound freedom to return the world to the power of the people, while facing the shadowy Supremacy and the unlikely foes of the Inheritors! We've built up the SUPERPOWERS universe, and now watch it be torn down! Featuring issues 0-6 in one trade paperback collection! Read it here and find out why everyone's talking about Project Superpowers.

Collects Project Superpowers: Chapter Two #1-6.
name: Vol. 1

description: The incredible story of Project Superpowers concludes here! Collecting issues 7-12 of the acclaimed series, creators Alex Ross and Jim Krueger clear the decks and set the stage for more thrilling adventures to come! In these issues you'll find out the ultimate fate of our heroes, witness the re-birth of the Claw and watch as the mad god Zeus wreaks havoc across the world! Plus: the birth of a new world order and a shocking twist in the story of The Supremacy!
name: Vol. 2

description: Pet Monsters were a hot new fad, but now they're rampaging through the streets! Who would sell zombies to a nine year old? And can the Penguin Rangers stop the chaos before their own toy sales plummet?

Through the development of aetheric technology, High London is about to become a floating island in the sky! But the Empire has made many enemies on its way to the top, and someone is trying to stop them. Now, Lady Penelope Ayre and her covert team of guardians, the Owls, must protect London at all costs!

volume.name: Victorian Secret Agents: Owls of the Ironwork Isle

description: Les “Survivorman” Stroud has accepted the challenge of tracking down a vital early American artifact known as “The Horn of Providence.” He will have to use his survival instincts and trademark problem solving skills as he battles the Horn’s captor: Oswald Wood. Les, his son Logan, and trust sidekick CroMagnon will wok as a team to bring the horn bak to its rightful owner.
name: The Horn of Providence

description: Tribute: Frank Baum tells the story of one of the greatest childrens authors of the 20th Century. Read about Baum's upbringing in a small town in New York State, his work in the theatre and his move to HollyWood to work in film. Witness the creation of one of the most beloved children's novels of all time The Wonderful Wizard of Oz. cover by famed artist Mario Gully!

volume.name: Tribute: L. Frank Baum The Wizard of Oz

description: The all-new Aoi House short story featuring the origin of Stephanie Kane from Vampire Cheerleaders/Paranormal Mystery Squad!

With a nuclear bomb headed straight for Zombie Ground Zero, the Wrecking Crew must escape San Diego in search of a mysterious government compound that supposedly houses the contagion's cure! But does new WC member Kurt Kiel have the group's best interests at heart, or does he have more sinister motives? This third volume collects issues 9-12 for fans of hilarious horror mashups like ZOMBIELAND and SHAUN OF THE DEAD.
name: Volume 3

description: The mutants have proven their worth, and Utopia thrives - but at what cost? Kitty makes a choice that could haunt her forever as Mach Two's jungle insurgency gains strength! Meanwhile, there are eyes in the sky - but who's watching the mutants? And when the new nation comes under siege, with General Ross leading the charge, Jimmy Hudson prepares for war - and Kitty and Mach Two must work together for the good of mutantkind! The big battle for Utopia is here - but when the dust clears, who will lead the mutant nation? Plus: Kitty Pryde faces off against Jean Grey, and we finally get some answers about Psylocke! Collecting ULTIMATE COMICS X-MEN #24-28.
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Ultimate Comics X-Men By Brian Wood

description: What are X-23's secrets? What is Darkhawk's big reveal? Secrets explode, alliances shatter, and Apex - the mean girl you love to hate - makes her move as the next chapter of the Arena's deadly game begins and the contest continues to take its toll! And as Nico makes a valiant stand against Sentinel, Hazmat strikes up a startling new romance - with Reptil?! Apex squares off in a bloody battle against an unexpected opponent, Death Locket gets a shocking eyeful, and Arcade... makes popcorn. What a jerk! The game is on, the stakes are raised, and the body count is rising! Plus: The history of Arcade is revealed! How did the former punchline become the sadistic scene stealer who now torments Marvel's teen heroes? Find out in this shocking behind-the-scenes story! Collecting AVENGERS ARENA #7-12.
name: Volume 2

description: In this title collecting GA #0 and 14-16, plus THE SAVAGE HAWKMAN #14 and JUSTICE LEAGUE #8, Oliver Queen crosses paths with both Hawkman and the entire Justice League! As if that's not enough, he must liberate Seattle's waterfront from the grip of Harrow, a thug who's running guns into the city! Also, Green Arrow's downward spiral begins as he loses Q-Corps, and discover the events that led up to the birth of Green Arrow in a tale from issue #0!
name: Volume 3

description: The Inhumans are one of Marvel's most enduring oddities. A race of genetic freaks living secluded in their island kingdom of Attilan, their mutations are self-endowed; as a coming of age ritual, each Inhuman exposes himself to the Terrigen Mists, a strange substance that imparts unearthly powers - some extraordinary, some monstrous. But now Attilan is under attack from without and within. Can the Royal Family, led by the mute Black Bolt, repel the foreign invaders who assail their outer defenses, as well as the internal threat of Black Bolt's insane brother, Maximus the Mad? Paul Jenkins and Jae Lee infuse one of Marvel's oldest families with a modern sensibility - including international politics, class dissension and the age-old struggle of growing up. Dark and grimly compelling, it remains one of Marvel Knights' most beloved stories. Collecting INHUMANS (1998) #1-12.
name: HC

volume.name: Inhumans By Paul Jenkins & Jae Lee

description: It's a new beginning for Iron Man as Kurt Busiek and Sean Chen reinvent the Armored Avenger! Tony Stark is back, with a new company, Stark Solutions - but the Mandarin plans to destroy Tony's dreams before they take shape! And if that's not enough, Iron Man must face Firebrand, Whiplash, M.O.D.O.K., Controller, Fin Fang Foom, Count Nefaria, the Exemplars, Ultimo and the new War Machine - while romancing the beautiful Rumiko Fujikawa and protecting his secret identity! Good thing he's got Spider-Man, the Fantastic Four and the Avengers to help him out! Collecting IRON MAN (1998) #1-25, CAPTAIN AMERICA (1998) #8, QUICKSILVER #10, AVENGERS (1998) #7, IRON MAN & CAPTAIN AMERICA ANNUAL 1998, FANTASTIC FOUR (1998) #15, IRON MAN ANNUAL 1999, THOR (1998) #17, PETER PARKER: SPIDER-MAN (1999) #11, JUGGERNAUT: THE EIGHTH DAY and IRON MAN: THE IRON AGE #1-2.
name: HC

volume.name: Iron Man By Kurt Busiek and Sean Chen Omnibus

description: Rarely before and rarely since has comics seen a talent as innovative as Steranko. Blending together influences from Pop art to Salvador Dali and Will Eisner to Wally Wood, Steranko's boundary-breaking style is an incomparable visual language that continues to influence and inspire storytellers decades later. Now, for the first time ever, Marvel is proud to offer the complete Steranko NICK FURY, AGENT OF S.H.I.E.L.D. in one volume! Collecting NICK FURY, AGENT OF S.H.I.E.L.D. (1968) #1-3 and #5, and the Nick Fury stories from STRANGE TALES (1951) #151-168.
name: TPB

volume.name: Shield By Steranko: The Complete Collection

description:
It's the story that turned Spider-Man's world upside-down as a dying Dr. Octopus hatches his master plan for vengeance against Spider-Man: He will become him! When Peter Parker suddenly awakens to find himself trapped in the failing body of his greatest foe, Otto Octavius rejoices in the power and youth of his new form. Can Peter switch their minds back before his time runs out? Yes?and no! As Peter's story comes to a dramatic close, Otto vows to become better than his old foe in every possible way. Smarter, stronger - he will be the Superior Spider-Man! But even with his newfound sense of heroism and responsibility, can Otto survive his heroic baptism of fire against the Sinister Six? A new era of web-slinging excitement starts NOW! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #698-700 and SUPERIOR SPIDER-MAN #1-5.

Collects Amazing Spider-Man #698-700 and Superior Spider-Man #1-5.
name: Volume 1

description: In these stories from issues #0 and #13-18, a terrible betrayal forces Wonder Woman to make a deal with the gods who want her dead, and her 'family' grows larger than she could have imagined. Will the mysterious Orion help Wonder Woman rescue Zola's baby from the clutches of Hermes, or does he have darker intentions?
name: Volume 3

description: Look! Up in the sky! As superheroes continue to dominate the big screen, Comic Heroes devotes an entire 164-page glossy bookazine to exploring the comics that laid the foundations of the phenomenon. This high-quality guide features a run down of the world's top 100 favourite heroes - as voted for by you! - and celebrates the creators behind them, and the teams that continue to make them popular. With retrospective features from the Comic Heroes archives, plus brand new artist profiles, opinion pieces and detailed character histories, this essential bookazine is the perfect coffee-table companion for dedicated fans of superhero comics.

One of classic Hollywood's most famous scary men, Vincent Price made a name for himself in classic mysteries and thrillers throughout the 1940s, 50s and 60s. Now Vincent Price Presents comes to Bluewater Production in this new story called "Digging One's Grave".
name: Digging One's Grave

volume.name: Vincent Price: Museum of the Macabre

description:
Dying Wish begins! The most shocking Spider-Saga ever! Doctor Octopus is dying, but before the end he has a sinister secret to share with... Peter Parker!

Plus, Carlie Cooper finds herself in the talons of the Vulture!

Also, the Scarlet Spider is hunted by an old enemy!

Story and art by Dan Slott, Christos N Gage, Guiseppe Camuncoli, Tom DeFalco, Carlo Barberi, Chris Yost and Ryan Stegman!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #698, Sensational Spider-Man #33.2 and Scarlet Spider #6!

Logan and Box travel to London to begin the recruitment of a global army to take down the worldwide network of Thinkers, but they soon discover a terrible truth that at its core may be an ideological death sentence for the entire human race.

Newly chosen Autumn Gnome, Katrina, is searching for a wild animal to be her Red Knight but heads straight for trouble when she visits an isolated fishing island full of hungry cats and her only saviour is Barbadango, a lying, thieving bandit who is anything but heroic.
name: The Cat and the Gnome Chapter 1

description: There's a new face of crime fighting in Gotham City, but will this twisted creation do more harm than good? "I...Batman" part 2.
name: I...Batman, Part 2 of 3

description:
A new story begins! Deadpool tricks X-Force into igniting a gang war between the Kingpin and Tombstone – and you'll never guess why! Don't miss a full-length adventure from Daniel Way, Carlo Barberi and Ale Garza!

Featuring material reprinted from Deadpool #50-53.

The 'Avengers vs. X-Men' saga continues here! A furious Vision attacks Magneto! The Thing and Sub-Mariner clash!

Don't miss the action from Brian Michael Bendis, Brandon Peterson, Mike Deodato, Frank Cho, Jason Aaron, Stuart Immonen

Featuring material reprinted from Avengers #24.1, Avengers vs. X-Men #0, New Avengers #24-25 and AVX: VS #1.

volume.name: Heckle and Jeckle the Talking Magpies
Hägar the Horrible - Ol' Blue Eyes Is Back!

name: Der Bisontoter ; Der Trick des Medizinmannes
Con Job; Eating Elvis; Last Night; The Peasants

person_credits.name: Evan Dorkin
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

volume.name: Lewis and Clark and Transportation for a New Nation
Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude

description:
The Hulk battles his worst enemy: Bruce Banner! One will win, one will die!

By Jason Aaron and Whilce Portacio.

The Red Hulk encounters the Arabian Knight and confronts a strange new foe in the Middle East – the mysterious Sultan Magus!

By Jeff Parker and Patrick Zircher.

Collects:

  • Incredible Hulk #6-7
  • Hulk #44-45
name: Attack of The Manticore

description: Clark and Diana must work together to find Diana's mother, Hippolyta. Clark searches the D.E.O. whilte Diana distracts Bones. What other secrets are the D.E.O. hiding and what connection does Felix Faust have with Bones?
name: Olympus Part 7
